# Use Tailwind for styling

- Prefer **Tailwind utility classes** over inline `style=""` or new one-off CSS.
- Theme design tokens live in `resources/css/app.css` under `@theme`:
  - Colors: `--color-sv-*` → e.g. `bg-sv-navy`, `text-sv-gold-light`, `border-sv-stone-light`
  - Fonts: `--font-display`, `--font-body` → `font-display`, `font-body`
- Reuse existing layout/semantic classes: `.sv-container`, `.sv-section`, `.sv-page-hero`, `.sv-section-eyebrow`, `.sv-section-title`, `.sv-btn`, `.sv-form-group`, etc.
- Add new custom CSS only when a reusable pattern or component justifies it; otherwise use Tailwind utilities (including arbitrary values like `text-[0.95rem]` or `shadow-[var(--shadow-card)]` when needed).
